Appointment Assignment

Pradeep Jaladi

July 17th 2020

Given the fact that health care systems consumed about 20% of the U.S. Gross Domestic Product (GDP) in 2017, which correlates to hundreds of millions of doctor visits each year, it is inevitable that the occasional no-show appointment will occur. However, a significant number of missed appointments can equate to millions of dollars in lost revenue, especially in a hospital setting. According to a 2016 study, the average yearly no-show rate for primary care and specialty medical appointments is just under 20 percent - an astounding number that could mean significant revenue loss for health care systems, both large and small.

We will be analyzing the data set try to understand the factors which has a greater influence on the no show of appointment. By end of the article we will be predicting the model.

## reading the data with string as factors false
no.show.raw <- read.csv("medical-appointments.csv", stringsAsFactors=FALSE)


## fixing the column names
names(no.show.raw) <- c("PatientID","AppointmentID","Gender","ScheduledDay","AppointmentDay","Age","Address",
                       "GovtAid","Hypertension","Diabetes","Alcoholism","Handicap","AppointmentReminder","NoShow")

## converting string to date format for appointment schedule time and appointment date
no.show.raw$ScheduledDay <- ymd_hms(no.show.raw$ScheduledDay)
no.show.raw$AppointmentDay <- ymd_hms(no.show.raw$AppointmentDay)

## Factorize Gender, Government Aid, Hypertension, Diabetes, Alcoholism, Handicap, SMS_Received
no.show.raw$Gender <- factor(no.show.raw$Gender, levels = c("M", "F"))
no.show.raw$NoShow <- factor(no.show.raw$NoShow)

no.show.raw$GovtAid <- as.logical(no.show.raw$GovtAid)
no.show.raw$Hypertension <- as.logical(no.show.raw$Hypertension)
no.show.raw$Diabetes <- as.logical(no.show.raw$Diabetes)
no.show.raw$Alcoholism <- as.logical(no.show.raw$Alcoholism)
no.show.raw$Handicap <- as.logical(no.show.raw$Handicap)
no.show.raw$AppointmentReminder <- as.logical(no.show.raw$AppointmentReminder)
## Calculating the wait time for the appointment
no.show.raw$WaitTimeInDays <- as.integer((no.show.raw$AppointmentDay-no.show.raw$ScheduledDay)/24)
no.show.raw$ApointmentMonth <- month(no.show.raw$AppointmentDay,label = TRUE)

no.show.df <- no.show.raw
# Remove the Age less than o and greater than 100
range(no.show.df$Age)
## [1]  -1 115
#sum(no.show.df$Age<0)
#sum(no.show.df$Age>100)

no.show.df <- no.show.df[no.show.df$Age>=0,]
no.show.df <- no.show.df[no.show.df$Age<=100,]

## Check the appointment days, if the difference is greater than 365 days ignore it
no.show.df$WaitTimeInDays <- abs(no.show.df$WaitTimeInDays)
range(no.show.df$WaitTimeInDays)
## [1]   0 178
no.show.df <- no.show.df[no.show.df$WaitTimeInDays<365,]

split <- sample.split(no.show.df, SplitRatio= 0.8)

no.show.train <- subset(no.show.df, split == "TRUE")
no.show.test <- subset(no.show.df, split == "FALSE")
noshow.glm <- glm(NoShow ~ WaitTimeInDays + GovtAid + Age + AppointmentReminder + Alcoholism + Diabetes + Hypertension + Gender, data=no.show.train, family = "binomial")
